<BaseLayout title="Evals — Independently Tested, Measurably Better | AgentQ" description="AgentQ was evaluated across 68 metrics against 5 leading AI coding platforms. Highest score in engineering, backend infrastructure, security, and requirement capture.">

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       PAGE HEADER
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-12 md:pt-32 md:pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h1 class="type-display text-warm-black mb-4 max-w-[768px]">Independently tested. Measurably&nbsp;better.</h1>
      <p class="type-h3 text-warm-mid max-w-[768px]">Benchmarks test whether AI can write code, but they don't test whether AI can build software a real business can use. So we built a benchmark that&nbsp;does.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 1: TLDR — Headline Numbers
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="tldr-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="tldr-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-10">What the data&nbsp;says:</h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-4">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <p class="type-display text-forest mb-2" style="font-size: 40px;">97.7%</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">of requirements captured on the first attempt. Next closest:&nbsp;57%.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <p class="type-display text-forest mb-2" style="font-size: 40px;">12 hrs</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">to production-ready. Next closest: 26. Worst:&nbsp;60.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <p class="type-display text-forest mb-2" style="font-size: 40px;">15</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">questions asked before starting. Most ask&nbsp;zero.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <p class="type-display text-forest mb-2" style="font-size: 40px;">96%</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">accuracy between what we said was built and what actually&nbsp;works.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <p class="type-display text-forest mb-2" style="font-size: 40px;">#1</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">Highest engineering score across 68&nbsp;metrics.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 2: WHAT THIS MEANS FOR YOU
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="means-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="means-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-10 max-w-[768px]">You don't need to understand 68 metrics. Here's what&nbsp;matters.</h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Getting your requirements&nbsp;right.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">AgentQ captured 97.7% on the first attempt, where most platforms miss nearly half. This means fewer surprises. Fewer rebuilds. Less wasted time &amp;&nbsp;credits.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">What you see is what you&nbsp;get.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">Most platforms build beautiful interfaces with broken backends. AgentQ scores highest on backend infrastructure. No surprises,&nbsp;ever.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Getting to launch&nbsp;fast.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">AgentQ needs 12 hours of human work to reach production. The worst platform needs 60. That gap is the difference between launching this week and being stuck for a&nbsp;month.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Security.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">No platform is perfect, AgentQ included. But we score the highest, and then add human security review through Developer&nbsp;Assist.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Honesty.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">When AgentQ says a feature is built, there's a 96% chance it actually has been built. Some platforms are accurate only 65% of the&nbsp;time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 3: THE BENCHMARKS
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="bench-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="bench-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-4 max-w-[768px]">SWE-WebDev Bench: testing what matters in the real&nbsp;world.</h2>
      <p class="type-body-lg text-warm-mid mb-12 max-w-[768px]">Most benchmarks test whether AI can write a function or fix a bug. That tells you nothing about whether an AI platform can understand your business, build a complete application, secure it, and get it ready for real customers. SWE-WebDev Bench tests that. 68 metrics across 6 platforms &amp; 3 business&nbsp;domains.</p>

      <h3 class="section-label text-warm-mid mb-6">What it measures:</h3>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-10">
        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="type-h4 mb-2">Did it understand what I asked&nbsp;for?</h4>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">Requirement capture, clarifying questions, retention of specific details like date formats and currency&nbsp;conventions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="type-h4 mb-2">Is the code well-built?</h4>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">Database design, backend logic, frontend quality, code cleanliness,&nbsp;architecture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="type-h4 mb-2">Do integrations actually&nbsp;work?</h4>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">Payments, email, third-party APIs, background jobs, scheduled&nbsp;tasks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="type-h4 mb-2">Is it secure and&nbsp;scalable?</h4>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">Security vulnerabilities, access control, rate limiting, behaviour under concurrent&nbsp;users.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="type-h4 mb-2">Can it handle changes without&nbsp;breaking?</h4>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">Adding features without destroying existing ones. Developer effort needed to reach&nbsp;production.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="type-h4 mb-2">Is it business-ready?</h4>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">SEO, analytics, multilingual support, AI feature&nbsp;quality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="type-h4 mb-2">What does it actually cost to&nbsp;ship?</h4>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-warm-mid">Total cost including human effort. The gap between what the platform claims and what actually&nbsp;works.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Testing conditions -->
      <div class="card" style="background: var(--color-warm-black); border-color: var(--color-warm-black);">
        <h4 class="type-h5 text-off-white mb-3">Testing conditions</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 type-body-sm text-stone">
          <li>9 standardised prompts across EdTech, Field Service, and FinTech-AI</li>
          <li>80 embedded "canary requirements" that only survive if the platform genuinely understands the brief</li>
          <li>Deliberately varied prompt styles: vague founder descriptions, detailed enterprise specs, complex AI-native requirements</li>
          <li>Every platform received identical prompts under identical conditions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 4: FINDINGS
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="findings-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="findings-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-4">Four things every AI coding platform gets&nbsp;wrong.</h2>
      <p class="type-body-lg text-warm-mid mb-12 max-w-[768px]">No platform is perfect. Including ours. But the gaps between platforms are large, and they show up in the places that matter&nbsp;most.</p>

      <div class="space-y-12">
        <!-- Finding 1 -->
        <div class="finding-block">
          <h3 class="type-h3 text-warm-black mb-4">Finding 1: Most platforms don't understand what you're asking&nbsp;for.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">When you describe your product, most AI tools skip the hard part of asking for your requirements &amp; jump into building immediately based on assumptions they never bother to&nbsp;confirm.</p>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-6">AgentQ's PM agent asked 15 targeted questions across 6 rounds before writing a single line of code. Some platforms asked zero questions and started building immediately. The result: AgentQ captured 97.7% of requirements on the first attempt. The next closest captured&nbsp;57%.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-separate border-spacing-0 type-body" role="table">
              <thead><tr>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 pr-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">What we measured</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-forest comparison-col-highlight rounded-t-card">AgentQ</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Next closest</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Worst</th>
              </tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6 border-b border-warm-black/5">Requirements captured</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-forest/10 comparison-col-highlight font-medium">97.7%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">57%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">17.7%</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6 border-b border-warm-black/5">Questions asked</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-forest/10 comparison-col-highlight font-medium">15</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">5</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">0</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6">Conversational rounds</td><td class="py-3 px-6 comparison-col-highlight font-medium rounded-b-card">6</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">2</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">0</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <!-- Chart placeholder -->
          <div class="image-placeholder mt-6" style="min-height: 200px;"><p class="type-body-sm text-stone">Bar chart: Canary Retention Rate across platforms</p></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Finding 2 -->
        <div class="finding-block">
          <h3 class="type-h3 text-warm-black mb-4">Finding 2: Beautiful apps with nothing behind&nbsp;them.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">All six platforms scored within 6 points of each other on frontend quality (61–74%). The interfaces look comparable. Behind the screen though, the spread is enormous. Two major platforms scored near zero on backend infrastructure while producing polished-looking&nbsp;frontends.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-separate border-spacing-0 type-body" role="table">
              <thead><tr>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 pr-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">What we measured</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-forest comparison-col-highlight rounded-t-card">AgentQ</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Next closest</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Worst</th>
              </tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6 border-b border-warm-black/5">Frontend engineering</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-forest/10 comparison-col-highlight font-medium">68%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">74%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">61%</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6 border-b border-warm-black/5">Backend jobs</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-forest/10 comparison-col-highlight font-medium">49.3%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">29.7%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">0%</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6">Core integrations</td><td class="py-3 px-6 comparison-col-highlight font-medium rounded-b-card">67.3%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">70%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">21.3%</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <div class="image-placeholder mt-6" style="min-height: 200px;"><p class="type-body-sm text-stone">Scatter plot: Frontend vs Backend scores</p></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Finding 3 -->
        <div class="finding-block">
          <h3 class="type-h3 text-warm-black mb-4">Finding 3: Every platform needs human effort to ship. The question is how&nbsp;much.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">No AI coding platform produces truly production-ready software without some human involvement. Apps built with AgentQ needed 12 hours. The worst needed 60. That's a 5x gap. This is why we built Developer Assist into every&nbsp;plan.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-separate border-spacing-0 type-body" role="table">
              <thead><tr>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 pr-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">What we measured</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-forest comparison-col-highlight rounded-t-card">AgentQ</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Next closest</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Worst</th>
              </tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6 border-b border-warm-black/5">Hours to production-ready</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-forest/10 comparison-col-highlight font-medium">12</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">26</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">60</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6 border-b border-warm-black/5">Re-prompts needed</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-forest/10 comparison-col-highlight font-medium">0</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">2</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">8</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6">Feature gap (hours)</td><td class="py-3 px-6 comparison-col-highlight font-medium rounded-b-card">5</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">15</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">30</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <div class="image-placeholder mt-6" style="min-height: 200px;"><p class="type-body-sm text-stone">Scatter plot: Engineering Score vs Effort-to-Fix</p></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Finding 4 -->
        <div class="finding-block">
          <h3 class="type-h3 text-warm-black mb-4">Finding 4: Security is broken&nbsp;everywhere.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">AI-generated applications are systematically insecure regardless of which platform generates them. No platform exceeded 65% on Security Score against a 90% target. AgentQ scored highest (63.7%), but even that falls short. It's why Developer Assist includes security review before you go&nbsp;live.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-separate border-spacing-0 type-body" role="table">
              <thead><tr>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 pr-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">What we measured</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-forest comparison-col-highlight rounded-t-card">AgentQ</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Next closest</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Worst</th>
              </tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6 border-b border-warm-black/5">Security score</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-forest/10 comparison-col-highlight font-medium">63.7%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">51.7%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">31.3%</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6 border-b border-warm-black/5">Scalability</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-forest/10 comparison-col-highlight font-medium">54%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">43%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 border-b border-warm-black/5 text-warm-mid">25%</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6">Concurrency handling</td><td class="py-3 px-6 comparison-col-highlight font-medium rounded-b-card">42%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">34.7%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">6%</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <div class="image-placeholder mt-6" style="min-height: 200px;"><p class="type-body-sm text-stone">Grouped bar chart: Security scores with target lines</p></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Finding 5 -->
        <div class="finding-block">
          <h3 class="type-h3 text-warm-black mb-4">Finding 5: When we say it's built, it's&nbsp;built.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">Some platforms show a dashboard that says your app is complete when features aren't actually working. AgentQ's accuracy was 96%. One platform showed 35% of features as "built" when they weren't&nbsp;functional.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-separate border-spacing-0 type-body" role="table">
              <thead><tr>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 pr-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">What we measured</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-forest comparison-col-highlight rounded-t-card">AgentQ</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Next closest</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium pb-3 px-6 border-b-2 border-warm-black/10">Worst</th>
              </tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td class="py-3 pr-6">Claim accuracy</td><td class="py-3 px-6 comparison-col-highlight font-medium rounded-b-card">96%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">88%</td><td class="py-3 px-6 text-warm-mid">65%</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 5: FULL SCORECARD
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="scorecard-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
